Package: nbamen
Type: Package
Title: AMEN Model for Count Data with Negative Binomial Distribution
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2025-09-04
Authors@R: c(person("Gwanghee", "Kim",
                    role = c("aut","cre"),
                    email = "musagh08@yonsei.ac.kr"))
Maintainer: Gwanghee Kim <musagh08@yonsei.ac.kr>
Description: Implements Additive and Multiplicative Effects Network (AMEN) models for count data 
    using negative binomial distribution with MCMC algorithms. The package provides functions for 
    fitting network models with additive row/column effects and multiplicative latent factors, 
    including support for overdispersion. 
    Uses Procrustes matching for post-processing MCMC samples and provides comprehensive 
    model diagnostics including BIC, WAIC, and DIC.
License: GPL-3
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.5), MCMCpack, utils
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Suggests: knitr, testthat
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
LazyData: true
NeedsCompilation: yes
